Defendant Thomas S Handlos in court with attorney Eric Theodore Raskopf.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant pleads Guilty to Counts 1 and 2 of the Amended Information.   The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

Count 1:  3 months Jail - straight time

Count 2:  30 days Jail - straight time

Counts to run consecutive to each other, 5 days credit.  

TERM OF PROBATION:  2 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s; 
*No Use or Possession of controlled substances or drug paraphernalia;
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed;
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions;
*Prescriptions to be filled at same pharmacy;
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling;
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.

FINE and COURT COSTS: $1,355.50 as to Count 1 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

COURT COSTS:  $243.00 as to count 2 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00 as to each count (to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME as to count 1: 30 days, STAYED; to be used at agent's discretion.  Agent to determine with or without non working hours.  

Expunction is conditionally granted upon verification of completion of sentence, payment of all costs/fees and no new criminal law violations.
